msgid "### 9.1 Recommended Configurations"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"| Scenario | Input/Output | Deployment | NPUs | P Config | D Config | Max Batched Tokens | Max Num Seqs (P/D) | Max Model Len | EAGLE3 | FUSED_MC2 | FlashComm1 | Async Scheduling |\n"
"|----------|-------------|------------|------|----------|----------|-------------------|----------------|---------------|--------|-----------|------------|------------------|\n"
"| Short Seq High Throughput | 3.5K → 1.5K | 1P2D PD separation | 24 (A3) | DP8TP2EP16 | DP32TP1EP32 | 16384 | 128 / 128 | 32k | 3 | On | On | On |\n"
"| Short Seq Low Latency | 3.5K → 1.5K | 1P2D PD separation | 24 (A3) | DP4TP4EP16 | DP8TP4EP32 | 16384 | 128 / 128 | 32k | 3 | On | On | On |\n"
"| Long Seq High Throughput | 128K → 1K <br>（90% cache hit） | 1P1D PD separation | 16 (A3) | DP2TP8EP16 | DP2TP8EP16 | 16384 | 64 / 16 | 200k | 3 | On | On | On |\n"
"| Long Seq Low Latency | 128K → 1K <br>（90% cache hit） | 1P2D PD separation | 24 (A3) | DP2TP8EP16 | DP4TP8EP32 | 16384 | 64 / 16 | 200k | 3 | On | On | On |"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"> **Note**: The prefix cache hit rate for short-sequence tests is 0%; for "
"long-sequence tests it is 90%. Adjust `max-num-seqs`, `max-model-len`, and "
"`max-num-batched-tokens` based on your actual workload."
msgstr ""

msgid "### 9.2 Tuning Guidelines"
msgstr ""

msgid "#### 9.2.1 General Tuning Reference"
msgstr ""

msgid "#### 9.2.2 Model-Specific Optimizations"
msgstr ""

msgid "##### Optimizations Enabled by Default"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"| Optimization Technique | Technical Principle | Performance Benefit |\n"
"| ---------------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- |\n"
"| FullGraph Optimization | Captures and replays the entire decoding graph at once using `compilation_config={\"cudagraph_mode\":\"FULL_DECODE_ONLY\"}` | Significantly reduces scheduling latency, stabilizes multi-device performance |\n"
"| CPU Binding | Uses `--additional-config '{\"enable_cpu_binding\":true}'` to bind CPU cores | Reduces cross-core scheduling overhead, improving decode latency stability |\n"
"| Multi-thread Weight Loading | Uses `--model-loader-extra-config '{\"enable_multithread_load\":true}'` for parallel weight loading | Reduces model loading time |"
msgstr ""

msgid "##### Optimizations That Require Explicit Enabling"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"| Optimization Technique | Applicable Scenarios | Enablement Method | Technical Principle | Precautions |\n"
"| ---------------------- | -------------------- | ----------------- | ------------------- | ----------- |\n"
"| FlashComm v1 | High-concurrency, TP scenarios | `--additional-config '{\"enable_flashcomm1\": true}'` | Decomposes traditional Allreduce into Reduce-Scatter and All-Gather | Threshold protection: only takes effect when the actual number of tokens exceeds the threshold |\n"
"| Fused MC2 | TP ≥ 4 scenarios | `--additional-config '{\"enable_fused_mc2\": true}'` | Fuses multiple communication and computation operations | Recommended for A3; not applicable for A2 |\n"
"| Balanced Scheduling | High DP scenarios | `export VLLM_ASCEND_BALANCE_SCHEDULING=1` | Enhances scheduling capacity between prefill and decode | Currently disabled by default (`0`). Set to `1` only when concurrency ≈ DP × max-num-seqs. Disable for long-context scenarios |\n"
"| EAGLE3 Speculative Decoding | All scenarios | `--speculative_config '{\"method\": \"eagle3\", \"model\": \"/path/to/Eagle3/\", \"num_speculative_tokens\": 3}'` | Uses a draft model to predict future tokens | 1–3 tokens for long context; 3 tokens for short context |\n"
"| jemalloc Preload | All scenarios | `export LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu/libjemalloc.so.2` | Replaces default memory allocator to reduce fragmentation | Ensure jemalloc is installed in the container |"
msgstr ""

